        <div class="perex">
          <h1>CERIT&#45;SC</h1>
 <!-- Content -->
<p>The national Center CERIT-SC  (CERIT Scientific Cloud) offers<a target="_self" href="/en/Hardware/index.html"> storage and computing</a> resources and related services, including support for their experimental use. Center also participates in the<a href="/en/VaV/index.html" target="_self"> research and development</a> releated to the flexible e-Infrastructures and it also <strong>colaborates in research activities of its partners</strong>.</p>
<p>Center CERIT-SC is created through transformation of the <a target="_self" href="/cs/about/History/index.html">Supercomputing Center Brno (SCB)</a>, a part of the <a target="_blank" href="http://ics.muni.cz/">Institute of Computer Science (ICS, ÚVT in Czech)</a> at <a href="http://www.muni.cz">Masaryk University (MU)</a>.</p>
<p>Center CERIT-SC will ensure that the current available resources of 550 computing cores and 150 TB storage capacity will be enlarged till 2013<a href="/en/Hardware/index.html"> to more than 3500 cores and around 3,5 PB storage</a>. All this capacity will be available on an open access principle, both as a part of the National Grid infrastructure and through cloud and other, even experimental interfaces.</p>
<p>Center CERIT-SC is an important part of the national e-Infrastructure, a complex system of mutually interconnected networks, computing, and storage resources and corresponding services for the Czech research community. This role of the Centrum CERIT-SC is explicitly mentioned in the <a href="http://www.msmt.cz/vyzkum/schvaleny-text-cestovni-mapy">Roadmap of large infrastructures for research, development, and innovations in the Czech Republic</a>. CERIT-SC resources and services offered and its research targets complement two other parts of the approved national e-Infrastructure &ndash; <a href="http://www.cesnet.cz">CESNET</a> and the <a href="http://www.it4i.eu">supercomputing center IT4Innovations</a>.</p>
<h2>Activities</h2>
